Privacy Policy for SnapMyShift

Effective Date: April 12, 2026

SnapMyShift helps users scan work schedules, create alarms, manage shifts, and export schedules to their calendar.

Information We Access

SnapMyShift may request access to:

• Camera, to capture schedule images for scanning
• Photos or selected media, if the user chooses an image from their device
• Calendar access, if the user chooses to export shifts
• Notifications, alarms, and exact alarm permissions for reminders
• Device identifiers used to manage subscriptions, usage limits, and account features

How We Use Information

We use information to:

• Scan and process work schedule images
• Extract shift details using AI-powered processing
• Create alarms, reminders, and notifications
• Export shifts to the user’s calendar
• Manage subscriptions, free trials, and Founder access
• Prevent abuse, enforce scan limits, and improve app reliability

Image Processing

When users scan a schedule, images may be securely transmitted to backend services and AI processing providers in order to extract schedule information.

Images are processed only for schedule-reading functionality.

Subscriptions and Billing

Premium subscriptions, trials, and purchases are handled through Google Play Billing. SnapMyShift does not directly store or process credit card information.

Founder Access Terms

Founder Access is a limited one-time purchase available to the first 12 qualifying users.

Founder Access grants lifetime premium access under the current SnapMyShift premium subscription model and feature set available at the time of purchase.

SnapMyShift may introduce new optional features, services, integrations, enterprise functionality, cloud features, AI systems, or separately licensed products in the future that may not be included as part of Founder Access.

Founder Access is non-transferable, tied to the original qualifying account, and may be revoked in cases of fraud, abuse, chargebacks, platform policy violations, or attempts to bypass usage protections.

Data Storage

Some information may be stored locally on the user’s device, including:

• Saved schedules
• Alarm settings
• Preferences

Certain account-related information may also be securely stored on backend systems used to operate app features, including:

• Device identifiers
• Subscription status
• Usage limits and scan counts
• Alias/profile information

Data Sharing

We do not sell personal data.

We may share limited information with trusted service providers strictly required to operate app functionality, including:

• AI processing providers
• Cloud infrastructure providers
• Subscription and billing services

Security

We take reasonable measures to help protect information during transmission and storage.

Data Deletion

Users may remove app data by:

• Deleting schedules within the app
• Clearing app storage
• Uninstalling the application

Users may also contact us with deletion requests.

Children’s Privacy

SnapMyShift is not directed toward children under 13.

